        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 1,
        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1523984013,
        "creation_date": 1523984013,
        "body": "<p>The LAF of a component is determined at the time the component is created.<\/p>\n\n<p>So you can try something like:<\/p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>set temporary LAF<\/li>\n<li>create components and add them to the frame.<\/li>\n<li>restore the LAF <\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>And if so is this a really bad idea ?<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Not sure if there are an hidden problems. <\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 49883566,
        "question_id": 49883521
    }],
